title: For Sale:  PHP-MV 1st Croatian Pistol 1990s, Became XD 15rnd 9mm All Steel NO IMPORT MARKS!!
postcontent:
Additional INFO--****All PHP Pistols imported through Century (all I have ever seen) are given a new electropenciled Serial Number on the left side of the frame different from the original on the right side of the slide and frame. This pistol has ONLY the original Croatian serial numbers on the right and NO large print new number like my other ones and every other.  Also, unlike the others listed on Gunbroker, NO broken grips on this one AND it DOES come with the xeroxed manual Century gave with their guns (It came with my other one)******* If you are a collector, or just looking for a proven, strong and reliable 9mm Hi-Cap pistol that was designed specifically for combat, this is something cool that none of your buddies will have. Very few will even know what it is. This one, like most of the imported ones, has superb bluing and finish for a military sidearm. There is about as close to ZERO handling or wear as you can get on an issued and surplused pistol. In fact, these are the finest surplus pistols that were issued that I have seen and I have owned almost all of them. An open slide design borrowed from Beretta that eliminates the common source of jams and the tilting block barrel mechanism from the Walther and Beretta designs. This pistol was redesigned into a polymer model in 2000 and then became the wildly popular Springfield XD, which you will notice, all say Made In Croatia. The mags from the XD-9 will fit this gun BUT there is a change needed to the little slot that locks it in (5 minutes with a dremel and tons of cheap mags available including 30 rounders, 20 rounders...). There are 2 online sites with original PHP mags as well. I have a copy of the manual they sent with these that I will send as well. I have shot my other ones, and when you find the ammo it loves, it shoots quarter sized groups at 10 yards. Double action, it is safe to store or carry with a round ready as the first shot is a long double action though you can cock the hammer for a light first shot. Here is a bit of history on this pistol....
By design, this pistol represents a mix between Beretta 92 and Walther P38 pistols. 
PHP (Prvi Hrvatski Pistolj - translates to First Croatian Pistol) is a different and interesting weapon which was developed in Croatia during its war for independence in early 1990s
The basic short-recoil operated action with vertically tilting locking piece is similar to both pistols, the general appearance of the open-top slide is close to the Walther but the single return spring below the barrel is apparently an Italian influence. Trigger is of traditional double action type, and the safety consists of a manual decocking lever, located on the left side of the grip frame. Magazines are double-stack and hold 15 cartridges. Other features and the appearance were similar to a Walther 38. Open slide design combined with a straight recoiling barrel lent itself to very good accuracy, along with elimination of possible jams of ejected casings. The slide, frame and smaller operating parts were milled out of solid blocks of steel, a procedure which was later dropped in favor of more economically feasible investment casting.

Desert Ghillie Sniper Suit
All pieces based on ACU pattern platform
Handmade Sniper Ghillie Suit
Low crawl Camouflage Desert Camo
Pictures are of Actual Ghillie Suit that is being sold

Not as light or pretty as the ones that are being mass produced for airsoft but is that what you want to trust.

 Ghillie Suits are camouflaged suits made of burlap, twine and similar materials that provide a high degree of concealment for military, hunters, and paintball/airsoft players. Although some ghillie suits are manufactured for sale, many military snipers and others make their own suits, both for the ritual and also for matching the suits to certain climates and terrain. 
 Every individual has their own traditional preferences. The single most important of these is an apparently strong desire to spend as much time as  possible crawling around. Extremely low profile and as little burlap as possible between them and the ground. The suits tend to be, simple with no particular frills, built on function rather than “gimmicks”

Military Suits have limited jute on the front (to discourage snagging) for low crawling situations

TOP

Hand built to assure that no signature (unnatural pattern) is evident 
Netting on the back and sleeves

The zipper on the jacket is covered , with the reinforced panel and  added Velcro to protect assembly
Heavy re-enforced front “crawl panel” ,with padding between it and the base, allows some comfort during stalking (heavy canvas material) 
Arm/Sleeves are also re-enforced with padding at the elbow and have removable/replaceable pads, not the thin issue style but heavy formed pads
One pocket on the upper part of each sleeve have been retained from the original top
Velcro tighteners at the wrist to adjust fit
